{"type":null,"faqId":46416,"title":"Huawei Watch_Can the Huawei Watch monitor my heart rate? How can I view my heart rate?","answer":"<a name=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414\"></a><a name=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414\"></a><div id=\"body1442371814966\"><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414__p66083391165317\">Yes. The Huawei Watch can monitor your heart rate.</p><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414__p57879615165317\">Swipe left on the watch's home screen and touch <strong id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414__b51154488165317\">Heart rate</strong> <span><img src=\"http://app.huawei.com/tkb/ha-i/73444_kdqma.png\"></span> to view your heart rate.</p><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414__p49872869165317\">Do not wear the strap too tight or too loose as this may affect your heart rate data.</p><p id=\"EN-US_TOPIC_0019757414__p46202643165317\">Test your heart rate when you have been resting for a while. The result should not be used for medical purposes.</p></div><div><div class=\"familylinks\"></div></div>","faqTypeId":328,"faqType":"Fitness and Health Monitoring","useful":0,"unUseful":1,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"en-us_topic_0019757414","faqTypeCode":"Wearable_Device-Sports-Health-Monitoring","isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1444638489000,"seriesProductName":"Mercury-G00,Mercury-G01,Mercury-G10","visitedTimes":123,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"heart rate, monitor, view","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}